The paper deals with information theory, probability theory, and optimization, which are all relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also introduces new concepts and establishes their properties, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability). The paper also involves optimization and convexity, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.MS (Mathematical Optimization). The paper also deals with fixed points and operators, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Dynamical Systems). Finally, the paper analyzes certain families of probability measures and channels, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Statistical Learning and Inference).
